Ramadan Kareem🌙✨
to everyone celebrating. كل سنة و أنتم طيبين

If you don’t know, Muslims around the world fast from sunrise to sunset every day for a month. To them, it’s a month of prayer, self reflection, & giving to charity. After fasting, families sit around the dinner table to break their fast together mostly while watching TV. 

Hence why Ramadan is like Super Bowl for the Middle East… All television personalities prep to produce their best shows/work this month as it has the biggest watch/follow rate. 

As a Christian born and raised in Egypt, it became tradition for my family to sit 6pm onward and watch a couple of shows together as a family, we even run to get snacks during the breaks and all! 

So Happy Ramadan Guys…

What are we watching this season? I have my eye on a few shows (Amina khalil’s, Menna Shalaby and a few more that look 🔥)

Let me know I wanna watch with you!

_

Do you color correct your videos?

There’s a huge difference always between raw videos and color corrected videos, they just come to life! What do you think? 

Here’s how you can do some basic color correction on your phone: On either @inshot.app or @capcutapp …

🌷Increase the vibrance (not saturation)(up to 10ish maybe).
🌷Increase contrast just a tad so ur video doesn’t get too dark.
🌷Then just add sharpness (1-5) is a sweet spot, don’t add too much so you’re videos don’t look pixelated and just look sharp enough for IG.

Which app do you use if u edit on your phone? If you’re editing on premiere or AE you have so many more fun tools to use but this is just quick and easy way on your phone.

If you have a 6 hours layover, would you go out or stay in the airport? 

My first flight to Egypt was delayed which made me miss my 2nd flight, the airline gave me another flight 6 hours later! There was no way I was going to stay in the airport, it was time to explore.

If you take the train for 1 hour or less from the airport towards Piccadilly Circus… This is what you can see: 

1.Piccadilly circus
2.China town
3.Trafalgar square
4.Treasury Horseguards road
5.Red buses
6.Big Ben
7.London eye 
8.Westminster Abbey
9.Walk through St.James park to end your walking tour with 👇
10.Buckingham palace 

👉Save & share with a friend you want to go with… London is absolutely gorgeous.

As I highly encourage you to go out and explore always there are a few things to be mindful of: 

1. Check if your passport allows you to enter this country & exit.
2.Ask/look up the nearest attractions that you can do in an hour or 2 max. so you can head back in time.
3.Make sure there’re no issues with public transportation, for example there were protests in London and they advised me at the airport to keep this in mind and come back early just in case.

Happy exploring 🙌

#London #picadillycircus #BigBen #layover #spontaneous #UK #welivetoexplore #ThisisLondon

Welcome to El Asala, العسلة. 

This is the definition of… OFF THE BEATEN PaTH.

This humble fishing village literally translates to “The sweetie” in Arabic. It is 15 mins walking from famous DAHAB town in Sinai. DAHAB is known to be Egypt’s most treasured diving destinations and if you’re in El Asala… you get the Red Sea to yourself & you’re so close to Dahab and the strip you can go back to the busy area anytime.

Why do I say humble? Cause the village doesn’t have much to do, you are surrounded by the Red Sea, a few fish restaurants (really good fresh catch of the day), humble simple homes… & the desert but it’s such a vibe. 🤍

Why would you go there?
1. To relax… connect with nature and find peace.
2. Swim in these light blue pools and snorkel in the darker ones past them… so many breathtaking fish & coral in the Red Sea.
3. Eat some fresh fish.
4. Spend practically peanuts… this hotel room is about $30 per person.
5. It is 10mins by boat to the BLUE HOLE, one of the best diving spots in the world.

Have you heard of El Asala village before? would you go?

Yes! This actually happened!!

Story time:
My fiancé and I got engaged in 2019, then shortly after the pandemic we started planning our wedding. 

It took me over a year to plan it. I really just wanted a pretty outdoor venue… like an old Italian backyard wedding, the options are so slim you would be surprised. 

But not going to lie, as a first generation immigrant in NY, I had to be extremely mindful of my budget because the prices here are just outrageous, and you’re really not getting that much in return.

After a lot of research, I finally found a beautiful venue and went ahead and got THE DATE. 

Shortly after, I traveled to Egypt to celebrate my sister’s wedding… planning to share the big news with my family & friends…

 But then I get this dreadful phone call that the venue is canceling on us due to issues with the county. I was in utter shock! Cried my eyes out and was just not too sure where to go from here.

Since then, my fiancé and I looked at venues outside the country and we were able to book the wedding venue of our dreams! Somewhere we never thought possible!

👉Tune in for part 2!

What would you do? Let me know your thoughts and if you had any wedding nightmares as well please share.

SAVE this video for your next trip to Atlantic City & SHARE with friends you want to go with.

I have recently been to AC and it changed so much from the last time I was there years ago… Everyone usually goes to the beach, walks the boardwalk, eats and gambles at night… 

Here’s a very different itinerary for you to try on your next trip:

👉1.Stay at @theoceanac and enjoy their spa “Exhale Ocean” …voted #1 spa in NJ.

👉2.Get Breakfast/Brunch at Hash House A Go Go @tropicanaac and indulge in their deliciously twisted farm food with huge portions!

👉3.Spend the Day @theshowboatac’s @acislandwaterpark the world’s largest indoor beachfront Waterpark and the newest attraction in Atlantic City fit for all ages.

👉4.No need to go far, Spend the evening @theshowboatac’s Lucky Snake Arcade, the largest arcade in the East Coast, with over 300 arcade games and indoor go cart racing. 

👉5.If you still have energy, head to one of the below bars for drinks… you can’t go wrong!
📍Carousel Bar @ballysac 
📍Old Homestead Steakhouse @borgataac 
📍Nola’s bar & Lounge @theoceanac 

We had an absolute blast, feel free to reach out if you need help with your itinerary or head to @visit_atlanticcity for more fun new AC activities.

Ciaooo Italia!! 🇮🇹 
Made it to Milan for a quick stop on our way to Carrara to explore some hidden gems. 

This is the most impressive structure in Milan, here are 5 facts about it:

1.it’s the 5th largest Christian church in the world.
2.it has the most statues, to be exact…  3,400 statues, 135 gargoyles and 700 figures.
3. You can set your watch by its sundial.
4. It took 6 centuries to complete!
5.it is actually still not finished!

Really impressive to see in person, have you been?

#Milan #Milano #italy #italia #visititaly #HiddenGems

Pitigliano… i.e. Little Jerusalem is one of the hidden gems in Southern Tuscany.

SAVE & SHARE with someone you want to get lost there with.

Such a cute little quaint village carved from volcanic stone, sitting so picturesque on a hilltop, just driving up there the views are to die for and you can tour it in a couple of hours. 

How to get there:
1.Drive and add @termedisaturnia hot springs to your list.
2.Take the bus from other cities & towns in Tuscany such as Florence or Sienna or even from Rome.
 
STAY: for maximum relaxation, I highly recommend renting a car, staying at @termedisaturnia and soaking in the hot springs then taking a drive to all nearby gems like Pitigliano daily. have you heard of it before?

PRO TIP: hire a guide or sign up for a walking tour, it will add so much to your experience and they can show u all the hidden spots.
